KPC LifeSupport License v1.0
Copyright (c) 2026 KPC Classics Conservation Program contributors

This software is part of the KPC LifeSupport mod series, which exists to
keep abandoned and at-risk games runnable. The license below is written
in plain language. The plain-language wording is binding.


1. WHAT YOU CAN DO

You may, free of charge:

  (a) use the Software, in source or binary form, for any purpose;
  (b) study, modify, and create derivative works of the Software;
  (c) distribute the Software, modified or unmodified, in source or
      binary form, to any number of recipients, free of charge;
  (d) integrate the Software with other software, including software
      under different licenses, provided those other licenses are
      compatible with this one for the resulting combined work;
  (e) port the Software to other platforms or other versions of the
      target game.


2. WHAT YOU MUST DO

  (a) Keep the original copyright notice, this license text, and any
      attribution to original contributors with every copy and every
      derivative work, both source and binary.
  (b) Make it clearly identifiable that a derivative work is a
      derivative — do not pass off modifications as the original.
  (c) State, in any user-visible documentation of a derivative work,
      that the work is based on KPC LifeSupport.


3. WHAT YOU MAY NOT DO

  (a) You may NOT sell the Software on its own, in any form, for any
      price. This explicitly includes:
      - listing it for sale on any storefront;
      - making access conditional on a one-time purchase;
      - placing it behind a recurring payment, subscription, donation
        wall, Patreon tier, "early access" program, paid Discord, or
        any equivalent mechanism that gates the Software, its updates,
        or its source on payment.
  (b) You may NOT bundle the Software with paid services or paid
      content in a way that effectively monetises access to the
      Software, even if the Software is nominally "free."
  (c) You may NOT misrepresent the origin of the Software or remove
      attribution to original contributors.


4. THE BUNDLED-WITH-THE-GAME EXCEPTION

The single exception to clause 3(a) is this: the rights holder of the
target game, or a distributor authorised in writing by the rights
holder (for example a digital storefront such as GOG or Steam acting
on the publisher's behalf), MAY distribute the Software for
consideration **only** when it is bundled together with a legitimately
licensed copy of the target game it patches, and **only** as a
component of that combined product. Even in that case:

  (a) the bundled copy must keep this LICENSE file and all attribution
      intact;
  (b) the Software MUST also remain available, in source and binary
      form, free of charge, from its public release page (this is so
      that the bundled-game distribution cannot become the only way to
      get the patch);
  (c) modifying the Software to remove its free public availability,
      or to add an authentication / online check tying it to a
      specific paid distribution, is not permitted under this
      exception and remains a violation of clause 3(a).

This exception exists so that, if an original publisher or storefront
chooses to adopt KPC LifeSupport patches as part of an official re-
release, they can do so without the legal friction of a strict
non-commercial clause — while still preventing third parties from
profiteering off the preservation work.


5. THIRD-PARTY COMPONENTS

The binary distributions of this Software may include or link against
third-party components under their own licenses. These components are
governed by their own terms, NOT by this license. Known components and
their licenses include, without limitation:

  - libmpv (https://mpv.io)              — LGPL-2.1-or-later
  - FFmpeg (https://ffmpeg.org)          — LGPL-2.1-or-later or GPL-2.0-or-later
                                            depending on build configuration
  - MinHook (vendored)                   — BSD 2-Clause
  - Ultimate ASI Loader (when bundled)   — MIT (© ThirteenAG)

When you redistribute a binary that includes any of these components,
you must also comply with their licenses (typically: keep their
copyright notices, ship their license text, and respect their source-
availability obligations where applicable).


6. NO WARRANTY

The Software is provided "AS IS", without warranty of any kind,
express or implied, including but not limited to the warranties of
merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and noninfringement.
In no event shall the authors or copyright holders be liable for any
claim, damages, or other liability, whether in an action of contract,
tort, or otherwise, arising from, out of, or in connection with the
Software or the use or other dealings in the Software.


7. SPIRIT

The intent of this license is simple:
  - Anyone may use the work, build on it, and share it.
  - Original credit must stay intact.
  - Nobody may turn it into a paid product on its own — neither sold
    outright nor gated behind a subscription, donation tier, or
    paywall of any kind.
  - The one exception is an authorised re-release where the patch is
    one component of a legitimately licensed copy of the game.

If a use case falls between the lines of clauses 1–6, refer to this
clause 7. The plain intent governs.
